    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 28th with a clear hierarchy in the outfield, anchored by the elite tier production of **Yordan Alvarez** (86.40) and **Kyle Schwarber** (78.40). **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a massive 16% park factor boost against the right-handed Baz, while **Kyle Schwarber** leverages an elite xwOBA profile and strong BvP history against Mahle. However, the most compelling start is **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (77.86); despite the \"Lineup Pending\" status and a lower spot in the order, his combination of favorable park/pitcher interaction and a high-probability SB environment against the vulnerable Buehler (xERA 5.19) makes him an essential play. We are intentionally overweighting **Pete Crow-Armstrong** today to capitalize on the scarcest category in our 5x5 format.\n\n**Trea Turner** (74.90) remains a cornerstone, with the optimizer highlighting his ability to overcome a slight penalty from a quick-release opposing catcher, driven by his high-leadoff-order value. On the infield, **Junior Caminero** (72.81) rounds out our top-tier plays, showing strong efficiency against Bibee. The most difficult decision rested on the middle infield bench; **Caleb Durbin** (49.05) barely secured his start over potential utility depth. While **Caleb Durbin** faces a suppressive batting order penalty (hitting 9th), his base projection kept him ahead of the remaining bench options. We continue to monitor the statuses of **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar**, both of whom remain sidelined, while **Zac Veen** and **Colt Keith** remain outside the active rotation as we wait for shifts in roster flexibility or performance variance.",
